\h STANCE \d

\uUSAGE\n
!stance \s[\dstance\s]\d

\uDESCRIPTION\n
Display or change your combat stance.

This command may take the following forms:
\qstance\d (with no arguments) to display your stance.4`
\qstance offensive\d (or just \qstance o\d) to take an offensive stance (that is, to favor offense at the expense of defense).4`
\qstance neutral\d (or just \qstance n\d) to take a neutral (balanced) stance.4`
\qstance defensive\d (or just \qstance d\d) to take a defensive stance (that is, to favor defense at the expense of offense).4`

\uSEE ALSO\n
attack
